Tingopix — Licensing
====================

Copyright (c) 2026 Pablo Miliani / Tingopix

This project is released under three licenses, each covering a different kind
of work. Where a directory contains its own LICENSE file, that file governs
the contents of that directory.


Software and firmware — MIT
---------------------------
Covers all source code, including:

    software-rpi/     Raspberry Pi scanner application
    postprocess/      offline post-scan processing tool
    firmware/         microcontroller firmware (when published)
    install.sh        installer

Full text is reproduced at the end of this file, and in the LICENSE file of
each directory listed above. Individual source files carry the SPDX
identifier `MIT` in their header.


Hardware — CERN-OHL-P v2
------------------------
Covers hardware designs, CAD files and bills of materials:

    hardware/         mechanical and electronic design (when published)

Full text will be provided in hardware/LICENSE. See:
https://cern-ohl.web.cern.ch/


Documentation — CC BY 4.0
-------------------------
Covers documentation regardless of which directory it resides in, including
README files, build guides and user documentation. This applies even where
the surrounding directory is licensed MIT: the code is MIT, the prose
documenting it is CC BY 4.0.

Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode


